Second Department,

August, 1950.

(August 14, 1950.) In the Matter of Louis J. Caligiuri, Respondent, against Jule L. Maisel, Appellant, and William J. Heffernan et al., Constituting the Board of Elections of the City of New York, Respondents. In the Matter of Louis J. Caligiuri, Respondent, against Jessie Maisel, Appellant, and William J. Heffernan et al., Constituting the Board of Elections of the City of New York, Respondents.

Order affirmed, without costs. No opinion. Permission to appeal to the Court of Appeals is hereby granted. Nolan, P. J., Adel, Sneed and Wenzel, JJ., concur; MacCrate, J., not voting. [197 Misc. 1000.]
